<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1158,1183]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Extensive membranous area between segment 
<number box="[829,843,1159,1183]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="8.0">8</number>
and terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1127,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[1095,1127,1158,1183]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cercus wide basally and gradually tapering towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[585,672,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[641,672,1194,1219]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonocoxal apodemes very long, projecting well beyond anterior margin of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[459,632,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Figs 58, 60, 
<number box="[601,632,1230,1255]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme a unilamellar vertically flattened plate, ~ 
<number box="[1349,1384,1230,1255]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[477,649,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Figs 58, 60, 
<number box="[618,649,1266,1291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1158,2022]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,417,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,527,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,527,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,615,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[480,494,1339,1363]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face which bears fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[879,921,1375,1399]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
setulae; small vertical setae, contiguous with uniseriate postocular setae; occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<date box="[538,572,1483,1507]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
<number box="[538,551,1483,1507]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[887,922,1483,1507]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1228,1317,1482,1507]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1335,1424,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1482,1507]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; dorsum yellow, except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, posterolaterally above wing base on scutum and laterally on scutellum and mediotergite; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number box="[1422,1436,1591,1615]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[294,350,1626,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[368,455,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[423,455,1626,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[687,697,1627,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[731,765,1627,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[1160,1170,1627,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[1278,1312,1626,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">5X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[615,625,1663,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[647,681,1663,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.2">1.2</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[851,862,1663,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
, 5.0X as long as wide; femoral formula 
<date box="[1313,1383,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1925-07-01">
<number box="[1313,1327,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[1336,1365,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="25.0">25</number>
/ 
<number box="[1374,1383,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
+ 
<number box="[1400,1427,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="16.0">16</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,167,1698,1723]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="6.0">6</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[530,567,1699,1723]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.8">0.8</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number box="[1090,1104,1699,1723]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity. T 
<number box="[331,341,1735,1759]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[372,407,1735,1759]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[574,585,1735,1759]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number box="[1192,1206,1735,1759]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="2.0">2</number>
rows 
<number box="[1276,1347,1735,1759]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="15.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="14.0">14–17</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[471,481,1807,1831]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong apical spine. Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number box="[1365,1377,1807,1831]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[593,658,1842,1867]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[676,764,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[732,764,1842,1867]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane faintly yellow, veins brownish; R 
<number box="[1301,1309,1857,1871]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1318,1325,1857,1871]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[831,866,1882,1906]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.7">0.7</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[1168,1176,1896,1910]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1249,1257,1896,1910]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[1290,1298,1896,1910]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1307,1314,1896,1910]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="5.0">5</number>
fork angle acute (~ 
<number box="[256,288,1920,1945]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[588,593,1935,1949]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[603,612,1935,1949]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about 
<number box="[793,827,1920,1945]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as R 
<number box="[1008,1016,1935,1949]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[1053,1061,1935,1949]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[1148,1156,1935,1949]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally and diverging at extreme apex; vein R 
<number box="[534,542,1974,1988]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 2.0X as long as R 
<number box="[773,781,1974,1988]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending before at level of R 
<number box="[1312,1320,1974,1988]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~2.0X as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,712,1997,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[731,818,1997,2022]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[786,818,1997,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number box="[940,981,1997,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
and 
<number box="[1042,1056,1998,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish; tergite 
<number box="[1269,1283,1999,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish. Tergites with distinct setae on posterior margin; tergite 
<number box="[914,928,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number box="[1175,1191,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1336,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brown. Cercus wide basally and gradually tapering towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[878,965,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[934,965,188,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
); left and right cerci distinctly separated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[328,414,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[383,414,223,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
), distinctly setose on outer face. Epandrium rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1212,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[1181,1212,223,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
), scattered setae on outer face. Surstylus shorter than epandrium, with spine-like setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1192,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">Figs 59, 61</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium rather subrectangular in ventral view, without distinct setae (
<figureCitation box="[786,868,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig 
<number box="[837,868,295,320]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonocoxal apodeme very long, projecting well beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[628,817,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Figs 58, 60, 
<number box="[786,817,332,357]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite narrow, with a small median posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[356,441,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,441,367,392]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus sclerotized, extending just beyond hypandrium apex, with narrow membranous area apically lacking scattered spicules (
<figureCitation box="[621,709,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[677,709,404,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme a unilamellar plate flattened in vertical plane, ~ 
<number box="[244,279,439,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[691,875,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 61" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,553,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[155,1432,553,1925]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 61. Hemerodromia longilamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 56. habitus, lateral view; 57. wing; 58. terminalia, lateral view; 59. cercus, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 60. phallus, hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view; 61. Hypandrium, gonocoxal apodeme, ejaculatory apodeme and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252076/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">
Figs 58, 60, 
<number box="[844,875,439,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[900,1047,439,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[1067,1161,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1176,1320,439,464]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[1339,1432,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,238,476,501]" pageId="16" pageNumber="225">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
